'''Bedouin music''' is the music of nomadic [[Bedouin]] tribes of the [[Arabian Peninsula]], [[Sudan]] and the [[Levant]].<ref name="encarta">{{cite web |url=http://encarta.msn.com/media_701879079_761556449_-1_1/Traditional_Bedouin_Music.html |title=Traditional Bedouin Music |accessdate=2007-09-20 |publisher=Microsoft Corporation |work=Microsoft Encarta Online Encyclopedia 2007 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5kwPuxdAf?url=http://encarta.msn.com/media_701879079_761556449_-1_1/Traditional_Bedouin_Music.html |archivedate=2009-10-31 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> It is closely linked to its text. Songs are based on poetry and are sung either unaccompanied, or to the stringed instrument, the [[rebab]].<ref name="encarta" />
Traditional instruments are the rebab and various [[woodwinds]].

