{{Infobox Union |name= CMKOS |country= [[Czech Republic]] |affiliation= [[International Trade Union Confederation|ITUC]], [[ETUC]], [[TUAC]] |members= 772,000 |full_name= Bohemian-Moravian Confederation of Trade Unions |native_name= Českomoravská konfederace odborových svazů | image= CMKOS logo.jpg |founded= March, 1990 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Prague]], Czech Republic |people= [[Josef Středula]], president |website= [http://www.cmkos.cz www.cmkos.cz] |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''Bohemian-Moravian Confederation of Trade Unions''' (Czech: ''Českomoravská konfederace odborových svazů'', ''ČMKOS''; the ČMKOS use this English name: ''Czech-Moravian Confederation of Trade Unions''<ref>[http://www.cmkos.cz/homepage Czech-Moravian Confederation of Trade Unions] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120224064036/http://www.cmkos.cz/homepage |date=February 24, 2012 }}</ref>) is a [[trade union]] centre in the [[Czech Republic]]. It was founded in March, 1990 as the ''Czechoslovak Confederation of Trade Unions''. It was re-formed in 1992 as the ČMKOS.
