{{Infobox hotel | hotel_name = Columbus Hotel Monte-Carlo (previously known as Columbus Hotel Monaco) | logo = | logo_width = | logo_caption = | image = Monaco fontvieille.jpg | image_width = | caption = The hotel is located just away from the Fontvieille marina | pushpin_map = Monaco | location = 23, avenue des Papalins, [[Fontvieille, Monaco|Fontvieille]], [[Monaco]]. | address = 23, avenue des Papalins, 98000 Monaco | chain = | coordinates = {{coord|43|43|38|N|7|25|12|E|display=inline}} | coordinates_type = | opening_date = 2001 | closing_date = | developer = | architect = | operator = | owner = London & Regional | number_of_rooms = 157 | number_of_suites = 24 | number_of_restaurants = | floor_area = | floors = 9 | height = | parking = yes | website = www.columbushotels.com | footnotes = }}
'''Columbus Hotel Monte-Carlo''' is a 3-star boutique hotel located at 23, Avenue des Papalins in the [[ Monaco|Fontvieille]] area of western [[Monaco]]. It was created by Scottish hotelier [[Ken McCulloch]] in partnership with [[Formula One]] racing car driver [[David Coulthard]] <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/news/in-the-drivers-seat-david-coulthards-16330m-hotel-haul-1980367.html|title=In the driver's seat: David Coulthard's £30m hotel haul|date=23 May 2010|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=April date set for first opening in McCulloch's Columbus hotel chain|url=http://www.caterersearch.com/Articles/20/07/2000/28239/April-date-set-for-first-opening-in-McCulloch39s-Columbus-hotel-chain.htm|publisher=Caterer Search|accessdate=13 November 2012}}</ref> until McCulloch sold his shares in 2008 to concentrate in developing his Dakota hotels in the UK. Coulthard sold out to [[London and Regional Properties]] in April 2010.<ref>{{cite web|title=Coulthard’s Columbus in Monaco sold|url=http://www.rivieratimes.com/index.php/business-article/items/coulthards-columbus-in-monaco-sold.html|publisher=''The Riviera Times''|accessdate=30 September 2015|date=13 April 2010}}</ref> The hotel was opened on April 21, 2001 by [[Rainier III, Prince of Monaco]].
The interior of the hotel was originally designed by international designer [[Amanda Rosa]] (McCulloch's wife)<ref>{{cite web|title=Amanda Rosa Interiors|url=http://www.amandarosa.com/|publisher=Amanda Rosa Interiors|accessdate=13 November 2012}}</ref> in the [[cosy and boutique]] style with light colour palettes and natural furnishings of [[leather]], [[marble]], [[wood]] and [[Rock (geology)|stone]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.columbushotels.com/english/rooms/|title=Accommodation in Monte-Carlo - Columbus Hotel Monte-Carlo|website=www.columbusmonaco.com}}</ref><ref name="MCH">{{cite web|url=http://www.monte-carlomonaco.com/columbushotel.php|title=Monte Carlo Hotels|publisher=|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100308164454/http://www.monte-carlohotels.com/columbushotel.php|archivedate=2010-03-08|df=}}</ref> The hotel has 157 rooms and 23 suites, 1 apartment and a lobby bar. An extensive program of renovation started in August 2017 to be completed by April 2018. 13 studio & apartments and 1 penthouse will be created, along with the refurbishment of the 181 rooms and suites - Certified Clef Verte (Green Key) - <ref name="MCH"/>
The hotel and Coulthard featured in an episode of [[Piers Morgan]]'s travelogue series ''[[Piers Morgan on...]]'' looking at [[Monaco]].
