'''Lycée Français Victor Hugo de Port-Gentil''' is a French secondary [[international school]] in [[Port-Gentil]], [[Gabon]]. It serves ''[[collège]]'' (junior high school) and ''[[lycée]]'' (senior high school) levels, and was established in 1990. In September 2014, it had 325 students.<ref>"[http://www.lvhpog.com/lvhv2/?page_id=24 Présentation]" ([https://www.webcitation.org/6YFCYQUbU Archive]). Lycée Français Victor Hugo de Port-Gentil. Retrieved May 3, 2015.</ref>

The school is named after the 19th-century French writer [[Victor Hugo]].

