{{Culture of Gibraltar}} [[Gibraltar]] is a [[British overseas territory]] with many musical influences. [[Rock music|Rock]] based [[music]] is undergoing a [[renaissance]] with a multitude of local bands playing original material and covers. Local venues have begun accepting [[Gibraltarian people|Gibraltarian]] bands and those from nearby [[Spain]], resulting in a varied mix of live performances every weekend as well as some weekday nights.
Musicians from Gibraltar include [[Charles Ramirez]], the first [[guitar]]ist invited to play with the [[Royal College of Music]] Orchestra,<ref>[http://www.chronicle.gi/Features/Charles%20Ramirez/charles%20ramirez.htm ''The Gibraltar Chronicle'' Always a pleasure to perform in Gibraltar] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20030909225847/http://www.chronicle.gi/Features/Charles%20Ramirez/charles%20ramirez.htm |date=2003-09-09 }}</ref> and successful [[rock band]]s like [[Breed 77]], [[Melon Diesel]] and [[Taxi (Gibraltar band)|Taxi]].
The best known Gibraltarian musician is [[Albert Hammond]],<ref>[http://www.foghs.org.uk/nl/70.pdf Friends of Gibraltar Heritage Society Newsletter No 70 November 2004]</ref> who has had top 10 hits in the UK & US, and has written many songs for international artists such as [[Whitney Houston]], [[Tina Turner]] and [[Julio Iglesias]] among many others.
Concerts in Gibraltar by well known international acts have recently given local acts a showcase for original material in their supporting roles. These include [[Surianne]] supporting [[Suzanne Vega]], Sarah Howard supporting [[Steve Hogarth]], Jetstream supporting [[Ali Campbell]] and [[Jessie J]] and SuperWookie supporting [[Marillion]]<ref>[http://www.gibraltar.gov.gi/latest_news/press_releases/2007/10-2007.pdf Government of Gibraltar press release - Announcement of Marillion Concert] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081118191214/http://www.gibraltar.gov.gi/latest_news/press_releases/2007/10-2007.pdf |date=2008-11-18 }}</ref> at the annual [[Gibraltar Music Festival]].
==Notable Gibraltarian bands== *[[Breed 77]] - Internationally recognised [[Flamenco]]-[[Metal music|Metal]] band. *[[Taxi (Gibraltar band)|Taxi]] - [[Pop rock]] band formed by three of [[Melon Diesel]]'s former members. *[[Adrian Pisarello]] & the EC band - Acoustic [[Rumba flamenca|Rumba]]-[[Rock music|Rock]] with Flamenco and [[Jazz]] influences. * [http://www.jetstreamgib.com Jetstream] - Rock / Pop, Opened for UB40s Ali Campbell and Jesse J for the inaugural Gibraltar Music Festival in 2012. EP "Piece of the Puzzle" showcased and released at the 2014 Gibraltar Music Festival headlined by The Script
